HEADWORD: Isatogen
<hw>I*sat"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Isat</ets>in
+ <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A complex nitrogenous
radical, <chform>C8H4NO2</chform>, regarded as the essential residue of
a series of compounds, related to isatin, which easily pass by reduction
to indigo blue.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>I*sat`o*gen"ic</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> </wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

